    "engine air filter": "Petrol engine air filter at standard ASSYST inspection intervals.",
    "brake fluid": "24-month brake fluid renewal per Mercedes-Benz European requirements for W213.",
    "check brake pad thickness": "Hybrid regenerative braking extends pad life but inspections remain mandatory at each service.",
    "spark plugs": "Petrol engine spark plugs on M274-based PHEV powertrains follow standard extended intervals (60,000 km / 48 months EU orientation\u2014verify booklet).",
    "coolant": "Engine cooling circuit coolant per Mercedes long-life interval (near 150,000 km).",
    "high-voltage battery coolant": "Mercedes specifies separate HV battery/e-drive coolant circuit maintenance on plug-in hybrids; 120,000 km is a commonly documented major service point\u2014always use a qualified EV workshop and confirm in the high-voltage supplement for your model year.",
    "automatic transmission fluid": "9G-TRONIC integrated with hybrid motor: preventive ATF service near 60,000 km is a common specialist recommendation.",
    "coolant flush": "Supplementary engine coolant exchange at 120,000 km if not yet due for OEM long interval.",
    "intake carbon clean": "Direct-injection petrol PHEV engines can still accumulate intake deposits; address around 120,000 km if symptoms appear."
